SIMPLE: defer
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Defer
<hw>De*fer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Deferred</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Deferring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>differren</ets>, F. <ets>diff⟦eacute⟧rer</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>differre</ets> to delay, bear different ways; <ets>dis-</ets> +
<ets>ferre</ets> to bear. See <er>Bear</er> to support, and cf.
<er>Differ</er>, <er>Defer</er> to offer.]</ety> <def>To put off; to
postpone to a future time; to delay the execution of; to delay; to
withhold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Defer</qex> the spoil of the city until night.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God . . . will not long <qex>defer</qex>⟦br⟧
To vindicate the glory of his name.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Defer
<hw>De*fer"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To put off; to delay to act; to
wait.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Pius was able to <qex>defer</qex> and temporize at leisure.</q>
<rj><qau>J. A. Symonds.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Defer
<hw>De*fer"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧f⟦eacute⟧rer</ets> to pay deference, to yield, to bring
before a judge, fr. L. <ets>deferre</ets> to bring down; <ets>de-</ets>
+ <ets>ferre</ets> to bear. See <er>Bear</er> to support, and cf.
<er>Defer</er> to delay, <er>Delate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
render or offer.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Worship <qex>deferred</qex> to the Virgin.</q>
<rj><qau>Brevint.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To lay before; to submit in a respectful manner; to
refer; -- with <xex>to</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hereupon the commissioners . . . <qex>deferred</qex> the matter to
the Earl of Northumberland.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Defer
<hw>De*fer"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To yield deference to the wishes
of another; to submit to the opinion of another, or to authority; --
with <xex>to</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The house, <qex>deferring</qex> to legal right, acquiesced.</q>
<rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deference</ent>⟦br⟧
